News24 studied the scene of the crash that claimed the life of Bosasa chief executive Gavin Watson in the early hours of Monday. The accident occurred on the short stretch of Jones Road leading to the parking and drop off zone at OR Tambo International Airport. Watson was the only occupant of the vehicle, a Bosasa owned Toyota Corolla. His BMW X5 had broken down and was in need of repairs, Bosasa spokesperson Papa Leshabane said earlier on Monday. WATCH | Bosasa boss Gavin Watson killed in car crash Bosasa executive Gavin Watson was killed in a "horrific" car accident in the early hours of Monday morning close to OR Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg. News24 found debris from the crash still scattered along the side of the road, and no evidence could be seen that Watson applied the brakes or attempted to avoid the collision with a concrete bridge pillar. ALSO READ:  GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here.  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. 